<h1>Problem 152 - 2007 Iranian MO, P4 of 5 , G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>\(P\) is a point inside triangle \(ABC\) such that \(PA = PB + PC.\) Let \(B'\) and \(C'\) be the midpoints of arcs \(APC\) and \(APB\) respectively. Prove that the circumcircles of \(BPB'\) and \(CPC'\) are tangent to one another.</p>
